subsection.p:
Note that 
        m_2=\dfrac{-3}{2}=\dfrac{-1}{\dfrac{2}{3}}=\dfrac{-1}{m_1}

This relationship holds for any two perpendicular lines with slopes m_1 and m_2, as long as m_1\not=0 and m_2\not=0.

